	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=5628&mid=107750958335438>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=5628&mid=107750958335438>I Got So Ripped Off!!!</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=5628&mid=107750958335438#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Feb 22nd 11:13 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=92605><span id= >Agrio</span></a><br><span id=notbold>64 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.92]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>When I rolled my Zerker I went shopping to twink him out.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I saw a weapon with a 100% damage delay ratio and no level restriction for ONLY 10Kpp I jumped on it.  That was about a week ago and since then I have seen it auctioned many, many times for under 6K and once as low as 4k.  <br><br>To add insult to injury, I have hardly been using the Reaver b/c the damage cap at low levels prevents it from hitting as hard as it should.  Instead I've been using a Sword of the Crypt Keeper that I looted for FREE on an LDoN mission (has a 50HP lifetap proc that works at level 1).  <br><br>Although I'm sure I'll be happy with this when I reach level 20 and the last damage cap is removed, I really wish I hadn't paid that much.  <br><br>I jumped on this at 10K b/c I'm so used to buying weapons for my Monk - any Monk 2h'er w/ those stats would sell for much, much more.  <br><br>Anyone on Tholuxe Paells wanna buy a &quot;like new&quot; Reaver for 10k?........lol  </p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
